      • isProbeOnly

        public boolean isProbeOnly()
        Description copied from interface: InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        If true is returned, the InteractiveServiceProvider is instructed to only analyze the input data to see if an output may be produced. The provider will analyze the input and notify the callback via InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback.setProbeMatch(boolean) to return the probe result.
        Specified by:
        isProbeOnly in interface InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        Returns:
        true if the provider should only probe the input value, false if it should attempt to produce an output.

      • getProbeLimit

        public int getProbeLimit()
        Description copied from interface: InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        Returns the probe limit value. The interpretation of the value is specific to the class of InteractiveServiceProvider implementation. Example interpretations could be the number of bytes in a file or the number of files in a directory.
        Specified by:
        getProbeLimit in interface InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        Returns:
        The limit to be used when probing.

      • setProbeMatch

        public void setProbeMatch​(boolean match)
        Description copied from interface: InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        If InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback.isProbeOnly() returns true, the provider will invoke this method once it determines whether or not it may be able to process the input data.

        If InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback.isProbeOnly() returns false, this method will not be invoked.

        Specified by:
        setProbeMatch in interface InteractiveServiceProvider.Callback
        Parameters:
        match - true if the provider may be able to produce an output value for the given input value, false if no output value can be created.
